HEADWORD: Fraudful
<hw>Fraud"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of fraud,
deceit, or treachery; trickish; treacherous; fraudulent; -- applied to
persons or things.</def> <rj><au>I. Taylor.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fraud"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fraudless</ent>⟦br⟧
